.TH "ingenic_ecc_get" 9 "ingenic_ecc_get" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ingenic_ecc_get \- get the ECC controller device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct ingenic_ecc *" ingenic_ecc_get
.BI "(struct device_node *np "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "np" 12
ECC device tree node.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Gets the ECC controller device from the specified device tree node. The
device must be released with \fBingenic_ecc_release\fP when it is no longer being
used.
.SH "RETURN"
a pointer to ingenic_ecc, errors are encoded into the pointer.
PTR_ERR(-EPROBE_DEFER) if the device hasn't been initialised yet.
